{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QQMB4DFxPRNNdq6YJhdxDi","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\\paragraph{1993 A--1 \\textnormal{[\\texttt{integral-evaluation}]}}\n2\tA reference asserts the following value. Determine whether the\n3\tassertion is correct.\n4\t\n5\tThe horizontal line $y = c$ intersects the curve $y = 2x - 3x^3$\n6\tin the first quadrant at two points $x_1 < x_2$. Define\n7\t\\textsl{region~A} as the region bounded by the $y$-axis, the line\n8\t$y = c$, and the curve between $x = 0$ and $x = x_1$; and\n9\t\\textsl{region~B} as the region under the curve and above the line\n10\t$y = c$ between $x_1$ and $x_2$.\n11\t\n12\t\\textbf{Claim.} The value $c = \\dfrac{2}{9}$ makes\n13\t$\\mathrm{area}(A) = \\mathrm{area}(B)$.\n14\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f6a76b3d-bd0a-4004-9591-de0b99152d87","uuid":"3701b697-f83f-4f06-a545-d13c51bea3ee","timestamp":"2026-05-20T13:53:24.804Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/private/var/folders/pl/c57pb2_52t513h0r4dgr0ryc0000gn/T/fc_1993_A1__false__forced_textual__r0_k1phm2fz/1993_A1_false.tex","content":"\\paragraph{1993 A--1 \\textnormal{[\\texttt{integral-evaluation}]}}\nA reference asserts the following value. Determine whether the\nassertion is correct.\n\nThe horizontal line $y = c$ intersects the curve $y = 2x - 3x^3$\nin the first quadrant at two points $x_1 < x_2$. Define\n\\textsl{region~A} as the region bounded by the $y$-axis, the line\n$y = c$, and the curve between $x = 0$ and $x = x_1$; and\n\\textsl{region~B} as the region under the curve and above the line\n$y = c$ between $x_1$ and $x_2$.\n\n\\textbf{Claim.} The value $c = \\dfrac{2}{9}$ makes\n$\\mathrm{area}(A) = \\mathrm{area}(B)$.\n","numLines":14,"startLine":1,"totalLines":14}}}
